What this hopes to achieve:
Allow source dependencies on virtual source sets to affect the compilation of said virtual source sets thus allowing said virtual source sets to accurately reflect the common code being compiled Reduce friction in usecases where common dependencies do not exist or are not applicable, thus the stub API covers it Allow sources to continue working by attaching (all) original associated source files, lowest version first Perhaps allow picking the sources via the resolution results of the dependant source sets/targets, to allow source artifact transforms to properly transform the common sources
General note: The generated API stubs need not be binary compatible with the targets, as a Jar compiled against a stub should not be runnable This may be changed in the future to be stricter, to allow better compatibility with consumers not using virtual source sets
Implementation would involve:
Function inputs being different would mean finding the most applicable type that is a subtype of all input types Function outputs being different would mean picking the common subtype of both Kotlin should have synthetic properties in the @Metadata annotation to match migrations from fields to functions or vice versa Kotlin type aliases should be intersected via kotlin API files Need to make sure those are compatible in the JVM mode of the Kotlin compiler Groovy should have extension getX to match property migrations Annotations should be intersected in that we pick only the shared annotations between intersection members

What this hopes to achieve: 希望实现的目标：
Allow source dependencies on virtual source sets to affect the compilation of said virtual source sets 允许虚拟源集的源依赖影响所述虚拟源集的编译 thus allowing said virtual source sets to accurately reflect the common code being compiled 因此允许所述虚拟源集准确反映正在编译的通用代码 Reduce friction in usecases where common dependencies do not exist or are not applicable, thus the stub API covers it 降低使用场景中不存在或不适用常见依赖项的摩擦，因此占位符 API 涵盖了这一点 Allow sources to continue working by attaching (all) original associated source files, lowest version first 允许通过附加（所有）原始相关源文件继续工作，最低版本优先 Perhaps allow picking the sources via the resolution results of the dependant source sets/targets, to allow source artifact transforms to properly transform the common sources 可能允许通过依赖源集/目标的解析结果选择源，以便正确转换公共源工件
General note: 一般备注： The generated API stubs need not be binary compatible with the targets, as a Jar compiled against a stub should not be runnable 生成的 API 存根无需与目标二进制兼容，因为针对存根编译的 JAR 文件不应可执行 This may be changed in the future to be stricter, to allow better compatibility with consumers not using virtual source sets 这可能在未来变得更加严格，以便更好地与不使用虚拟源集的消费者兼容
Implementation would involve: 实施将包括：
Function inputs being different would mean finding the most applicable type that is a subtype of all input types 函数输入不同意味着找到适用于所有输入类型的最大子类型 Function outputs being different would mean picking the common subtype of both 函数输出不同意味着选择两者的共同子类型 Kotlin should have synthetic properties in the @Metadata annotation to match migrations from fields to functions or vice versa Kotlin 应该在 @Metadata 注解中具有合成属性，以匹配从字段到函数或反之亦然的迁移 Kotlin type aliases should be intersected via kotlin API files Kotlin 类型别名应通过 kotlin API 文件进行交集 Need to make sure those are compatible in the JVM mode of the Kotlin compiler 需要确保这些在 Kotlin 编译器的 JVM 模式下兼容 Groovy should have extension getX to match property migrations Groovy 应该有扩展 getX 来匹配属性迁移 Annotations should be intersected in that we pick only the shared annotations between intersection members 标注应相交，我们只选择交集中成员之间的共享标注
